    <item>
      <title>贝莱德罗森伯格：美联储降息 50 个基点仍是“高门槛”</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2024-11-01/50-bps-fed-cut-still-a-high-bar-blackrock-s-rosenberg-video</link>
      <description><![CDATA[贝莱德系统性多策略基金投资组合经理杰弗里·罗森伯格 (Jeffrey Rosenberg) 表示，美联储 11 月降息 50 个基点“仍是一个相当高的门槛”，同时他回应了 10 月份美国就业报告以及这对美联储货币政策的影响。他在“彭博监测”节目中发表了讲话。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2024-11-01/50-bps-fed-cut-still-a-high-bar-blackrock-s-rosenberg-video</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Nov 2024 13:19:16 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>十月份就业报告对美联储政策意味着什么</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2024-11-01/what-the-october-jobs-report-could-mean-for-fed-policy-video</link>
      <description><![CDATA[贝莱德系统性多策略基金投资组合经理杰弗里·罗森伯格在回应美国 10 月份就业报告并讨论其对美联储货币政策的影响时表示：“软着陆仍是关键信息。”他在“彭博监测”节目中发表了讲话。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2024-11-01/what-the-october-jobs-report-could-mean-for-fed-policy-video</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Nov 2024 13:09:14 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>分析师预计英国建筑商价值将在经历预算危机以来最糟糕的一天后回落</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-01/analyst-sees-uk-builder-value-after-worst-day-since-truss-budget</link>
      <description><![CDATA[摩根士丹利分析师表示，他们倾向于买入更多英国房屋建筑商的股票，此前该类股遭遇了两年前特拉斯政府小型预算引发的暴跌以来的最大跌幅。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-01/analyst-sees-uk-builder-value-after-worst-day-since-truss-budget</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Nov 2024 13:05:35 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>抛硬币式选举迫在眉睫，交易员认为黄金是稳操胜券的选择</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-01/traders-see-gold-as-a-surefire-bet-as-coin-toss-election-looms</link>
      <description><![CDATA[作为美国现代史上竞争最激烈的选举之一，金价飙升，引发了人们对避险资产的热潮，许多投资者预计未来金价将进一步上涨。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-01/traders-see-gold-as-a-surefire-bet-as-coin-toss-election-looms</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Nov 2024 13:00:52 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>美国 10 月新增就业岗位 12,000 个，低于预期</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2024-11-01/us-adds-12-000-jobs-in-october-missing-estimates-video</link>
      <description><![CDATA[美国 10 月份新增就业岗位 12,000 个，低于预期的 100,000 个。美国劳工统计局表示，飓风和波音工人的大规模罢工可能扭曲了数据。失业率保持在 4.1%，时薪保持稳定。Michael McKee 在“彭博监测”上报道。（来源：彭博社）]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2024-11-01/us-adds-12-000-jobs-in-october-missing-estimates-video</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Nov 2024 12:57:06 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>美国就业数据失真助长美联储降息预期，美国国债价格飙升</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-01/treasuries-soar-as-distorted-us-jobs-data-fuels-bets-on-fed-cut</link>
      <description><![CDATA[由于上个月风暴和罢工事件导致美国经济仅创造了 12,000 个就业岗位，且市场对美联储下周降息的预期保持不变，美国政府债务出现反弹。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-01/treasuries-soar-as-distorted-us-jobs-data-fuels-bets-on-fed-cut</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 01 Nov 2024 12:48:46 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
